CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, Philadelphia edition, May 11, 1940, pg. 15 reads: " No. 8 - Rev. George T. Sims directs affairs of the country's largest religious organization. One of the younger ministers of the African Methodist Episcopal church, who was elected general secretary  of the Quadrennial at Detroit, on Wednesday.  The Rev. Dr. Sims is pastor of St. John A.M. E. church, Montgomery, Alabama.  His election is an indication of the trend of the convention to elevate younger and more efficient men."
TitMainTitle: Reverend Dr. George T. Sims seated behind desk with unknown woman in office interior, possibly in Ebenezer AME Church, during AME General Conference, Detroit
